After joining the European Olympic family, Azerbaijan began to integrate into European institutions more rapidly.
Our political system is the model of European political system.
The membership of the Council of Europe, which took place in 2001, allowed us to continue reforms and promote European values ​​in our country
Political reforms are one of the main priorities for Azerbaijan.
Establishing strong democratic institutions is a prerequisite for us.
We have a strong economy today. But without a solid political system, our development could not be as fast as we wanted it to be.
All basic freedoms, including religious freedom, have been fully ensured in Azerbaijan.
Our country is one of the main centers of multiculturalism in the world.
We are working hard to build a modern, self-sustaining economy.
For this reason, economic reforms are a matter in our agenda.
Azerbaijan is a very important European partner in energy security.
We consider our relations with the European Union as a predictable, very strong relationship based on common values, mutual respect and interest
Today, the world needs more cooperation and understanding, as well as reducing existing and potential threats.
The steps we take throughout the country, our policies toward our neighbors and our partners are highly valued in the world.
We do a lot to promote Olympic values. These are the values ​​of friendship, peace and cooperation.
The European Games to be held next year will become the highest level sporting event for us.
We are proud that the first European Games will be held in Azerbaijan.
Our country is modern and dynamic, open to cooperation, located at the intersection of civilizations and continents, (cont) http://t.co/muXni7LZRj
